<br>
Now that is spin!<br>
<br>
The economic indexes were headed down even before the election, are you one of those that think the president snaps his finger and the economy just follows along? The economy tends (Read the word &quot;tends&quot; three times) to move slow and in cycles, in America the Presidential policies can influence it but that is about all.<br>
<br>
Here are some basic economics for you. In taxes the amount collected is in proportion to economic prosperity. Prosperity is is a function of consumer confidence, the willingness to make investments and large purchases. People are not going to make investments or large purchases if they have less money.<br>
<br>
If the government takes more of peoples money they have less to invest and spend on large purchases and the economy takes a hit.<br>
<br>
Rich people are not affected by tax cuts because most of their capital is in assets, high income earners are most affected by tax cuts, these are the people who motivate the economy, they are the ones who tend to put up investment capital.<br>
<br>
The poor are the most hurt by a poor economy, tax cuts can't help them because they don't pay taxes, invest or create jobs.<br>
<br>
Of the things that set me against the DNC the most is their tax and spend mentality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kithmir>Kithmir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/18/03 8:26:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clinton Speaks</span><hr size=1> Well said Siffo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Kithmir, High Elven Wizard<br>
