<br>
Since there is a limit to how much debt we can incur... a limit which we have almost reached... programs would then need to start being cut to keep us under that threshold.  Other option is to raise the debt cap.<br>
<br>
As I understand it, Dems have been pushing for an increase to the cap, Republicans are okay w/ progams getting axed.<br>
<br>
Our state (Washington) has had to cut programs because our state budget is in piss poor shape, it hasn't been at all pleasant.  It hasn't been stuff like rehabilitation for serial rapists that were cut, it's been programs like work programs for the developmentally delayed, etc.  Oregon has been cutting all kinds of health assistance.  Our school system &amp; teacher salaries have taken a huge beating as well.<br>
<br>
