ty college tuition doubled, too.  Police survelence in rural areas is way down in my state too.  But then again, a lot of our problems in CA come from the energy scandle, so while Federal Funding would have helped save us a lot of greif, we can't really blame that on the national deficit, just the state level one.  But the economics work similarly at the national scale.<br>
<br>
But the main thing with a deficit is that we have to pay interests on the debts... the higher our debts, the more taxes we pay just to pay down interest, instead of paying for things that we actually want, like road repairs or policemen or whathave you.<br>
<br>
A small debt is a good thing.  It keeps buisinesses tied to the government... read the Federalist Papers for details on that concept.  However, once we're at the multi-trillion dollar level, we have a serious problem.  You see, when we have deficit spending, we're borrowing money from our children.  Eventually, someone's going to have to pay the bill.<br>
<br>
